        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>At FinConnect ("we," "our," or "us"), we value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our app or services ("Service").</p>
        <p>By using the Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, please do not use the Service.</p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><span class="highlight">1.1 Personal Information</span><br>Name, email address, phone number, and other contact details provided during account creation or support inquiries.</li>
            <li><span class="highlight">1.2 Usage Data</span><br>Information about how you interact with the Service, including log data, device information, and usage statistics.</li>
            <li><span class="highlight">1.3 Financial Data</span><br>When you connect your QuickBooks account, we may process transaction details, invoices, and other accounting data to facilitate seamless integration. <br><span class="highlight">Note:</span> We do not store your financial data. All interactions with QuickBooks API are handled securely and directly.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the collected information to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Provide and maintain the Service.</li>
            <li>Respond to your inquiries and support requests.</li>
            <li>Improve and optimize the Service.</li>
            <li>Notify you of updates, changes, or promotions related to the Service.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Sharing of Information</h2>
        <p>We do not sell or rent your personal information. However, we may share information in the following circumstances:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><span class="highlight">With Service Providers:</span> To perform tasks on our behalf, such as hosting, analytics, or customer support.</li>
            <li><span class="highlight">As Required by Law:</span> To comply with legal obligations or protect our rights.</li>
            <li><span class="highlight">With Your Consent:</span> When you explicitly agree to share information.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no system can guarantee complete security.</p>

        <h2>5. Your Data Rights</h2>
        <p>Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your data:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access, update, or delete your personal information.</li>
            <li>Object to or restrict certain data processing activities.</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at <span class="contact-info">[Insert Contact Email]</span>.</p>

        <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>Our Service interacts with QuickBooks, a third-party platform. This Privacy Policy does not cover their practices. We encourage you to review QuickBooks' Privacy Policy.</p>

        <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>Our Service is not directed to children under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect information from children.</p>

        <h2>8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be effective upon posting. Your continued use of the Service after changes are posted signifies your acceptance.</p>

